-- U.S. Stocks Trim Advance as Tech Shares, Oil Turn Lower
-- Michael P. Regan
-- 2010-06-21T17:46:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/u-s-stocks-trim-advance-as-technology-companies-oil-producers-turn-lower.html

          
          
             U.S. stocks trimmed gains as
technology companies erased an early advance and oil turned
lower.  
 The Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index increased 0.2 percent to
1,120.16 at 1:43 p.m. in New York after surging as much as 1.2
percent in early trading. The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose
39.94, or 0.4 percent, to 10,490.58, paring most of a 144 point
rally. Oil slipped 0.2 percent to $77 a barrel after jumping as
much as 2.3 percent to $78.92  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          June 21 (Bloomberg) -- Donald Straszheim, senior managing director of China research at International Strategy & Investment Group, talks about the People's Bank of China's decision to end the two-year currency peg to the dollar and the impact on the stock market.
     Straszheim talks with Margaret Brennan and Scarlet Fu on Bloomberg Television's "In Business." (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
